STATE OF HAWAII C.D. 1
A BILL FOR AN ACT
RELATING TO MOPEDS.
BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF HAWAII:
1 SECTION 1. Section 286-81, Hawaii Revised Statutes, is
2 amended by amending subsection (b) as follows:
3 "(b) Notwithstanding subsection (a) [and-ocction 291C-
4 i^] , no person shall operate a moped or motor scooter leased
5 from a rental company on any roadway in the State unless the
6 person wears a safety helmet, which shall be provided by the
7 rental company unless the person provides the person's own
8 safety helmet; provided that this subsection shall not apply to
9 persons who possess a valid license under this chapter to
10 operate a motorcycle or an equivalent license issued from
11 another state. To meet the requirements of this subsection, the
12 safety helmet shall meet the specifications and requirements
13 established by rules adopted by the director."
14 SECTION 2. Section 291C-195, Hawaii Revised Statutes, is
15 amended by amending subsection (a) to read as follows:
16 "(a) Notwithstanding section 286-81 (b), no person:
